---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Ending in -FY — High-Scoring Verbs for Your Rack"
  description="Master Scrabble words ending in -FY with full point values. QUALIFY 22pts, JUSTIFY 20pts, MAGNIFY 16pts. Strategy for playing -FY suffix words in competitive games."
  keywords="scrabble words ending in fy, qualify scrabble points, justify scrabble, magnify scrabble word, fy suffix scrabble, high scoring fy words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Ending in -FY — High-Scoring Verbs for Your Rack","description":"Master Scrabble words ending in -FY with full point values. QUALIFY 22pts, JUSTIFY 20pts, MAGNIFY 16pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-fy"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is QUALIFY worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"QUALIFY scores 22 points (Q=10, U=1, A=1, L=1, I=1, F=4, Y=4). It uses the Q tile worth 10 points along with F (4pts) and Y (4pts). As a 7-letter word it qualifies for the 50-point bingo bonus."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is JUSTIFY a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! JUSTIFY is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS, scoring 20 points (J=8, U=1, S=1, T=1, I=1, F=4, Y=4). The J tile contributes 8 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best -FY words for Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Top -FY words are QUALIFY (22pts), JUSTIFY (20pts), MYSTIFY (18pts), MAGNIFY (16pts), and HORRIFY (16pts). These combine high-value consonants Q, J, F with the 4-point Y ending."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in -FY — High-Scoring Verbs for Your Rack</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Words ending in -FY are almost always verbs — and they're scoring machines. The F tile is worth 4 points, the Y tile another 4, so every -FY word starts with an 8-point foundation. Pair that suffix with Q, J, or X and you're looking at 20+ point plays from a single word.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">22 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUALIFY (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JUSTIFY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MYSTIFY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MAGNIFY</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring -FY Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">QUALIFY — 22 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Q=10, U=1, A=1, L=1, I=1, F=4, Y=4 · 7 letters · Bingo candidate</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">QUALIFY uses the Q tile (10pts) alongside F and Y (4pts each) for a massive base score. As a 7-letter word, it qualifies for the 50-point bingo bonus — turning 22 into 72 points in one move.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚖️ JUSTIFY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">20 pts · J=8, U=1, S=1, T=1, I=1, F=4, Y=4 · Rare J tile</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔮 MYSTIFY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 pts · M=3, Y=4, S=1, T=1, I=1, F=4, Y=4 · Double Y</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔍 MAGNIFY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · M=3, A=1, G=2, N=1, I=1, F=4, Y=4 · Common letters</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">😱 HORRIFY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · H=4, O=1, R=1, R=1, I=1, F=4, Y=4 · H adds value</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Mid-Range -FY Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VERIFY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MODIFY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PACIFY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TYPIFY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">17pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CODIFY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STUPEFY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for -FY Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold F+Y together:</span> The -FY ending guarantees 8 points minimum. Keep them paired and build around them. Most -FY words use common vowels (A, I, U) that are easy to draw.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo potential with Q or J:</span> QUALIFY and JUSTIFY are both 7-letter words. If you have Q or J plus F and Y, look for the connecting letters (UALI or USTI) for the 50-point bonus.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Shorter fallbacks:</span> DEFY (11pts) and DEIFY (12pts) are solid 4-5 letter plays that leverage F+Y without needing rare tiles. Good for tight board positions.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The -FY suffix is <span class="text-white font-medium">uniquely verb-forming</span> in English, hooking onto many roots. PURIFY, RATIFY, NOTIFY, OSSIFY — all valid, all scoring 10+ points base. Learn the pattern and spot plays others miss.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid -FY word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ry/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -RY</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-gy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -GY</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ing/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -ING</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ous/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -OUS</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ty/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -TY</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
